reporting-org.narrative: The Global Fund to Fight AIDS, Tuberculosis and Malaria

title.narrative: Program to strengthen the national response to HIV/AIDS in Niger

description.narrative: Niger - HIV - Cellule Nationale de Coordination Technique de la Riposte Nationale au Sida et aux Hépatites - CN/CTRN. This program has the following goals: Reduce new infections by 50%. Improve the quality of life of at least 80% of people living with HIV and 20% of the orphans and other vulnerable children (OVC) identified by 2020. Efficient governance of the national response to HIV / AIDS. The objectives of this program are: Reduce mother-to-child transmission rates to less than 5% by 2020 among children born to seropositive mothers. At least 85% of identified key populations adopt a lower risk behavior by 2020 (SW, MSM, Migrant Workers, Prison Population). Increase to 80% the 12-month survival rate of PLWHA children and adults diagnosed and placed on ARV therapy by 2020. Effective respect of human rights for at least 80% of PLWHA by 2020. Effective participation of community-based organizations in the national response to HIV / AIDS. Produce, use and make available quality strategic information on STIs and HIV / AIDS for the national response
